The '''Midob people''' are an ethnic group from the [[Meidob Volcanic Field|Meidob Hills]] region in [[Darfur]], [[Sudan]]. They speak [[Midob language|Midob]], one of the [[Nubian languages]] (part of the larger family of [[Nilo-Saharan languages]]). The population of this ethnic group possibly exceeds 50,000.

The Midob's roots go back to [[Meroë|Meroitic Kingdom]] ([[Kingdom of Kush]]) in Northern Sudan. Many historians like Brown (''The history Of Sudanese Tribes'') mentioned that Midob is the ruling family in the Nubian Civilization and their roots extends to the [[pharaoh]]s of [[Ancient Egypt]].{{fact|date=October 2013}}

